thread.title: Automotive Holdings profit up 21%

title: Automotive Holdings profit up 21%
text:
Fri, Aug 14, 2015, 11:32 AM NZST - New Zealand Markets close in 5 hrs 28 mins Automotive Holdings profit up 21% AAP – 40 minutes ago Print 
Australia's largest car and truck retailer Automotive Holdings lifted its full year profit 21 per cent thanks to new acquisitions and the ongoing expansion of its operations. 
Automotive made a net profit of $88 million for the year to June 30, up from $72.9 million a year ago, largely due its acquisition of Bradfield Motor Group and the expansion of its refrigerated logistics business. 
Revenue for the year was up nearly 11 per cent to $5.2 billion and the company lifted its final dividend half a cent to 13 cents per share. @YahooNZBusiness on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook AAP
